cs.NI, cs.MM, cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.CE

This paper deals with the analysis of Quality of Service (QoS) of VoIP traffic through WiFi and UMTS networks. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as it deals with the analysis of network performance. cs.MM (Multimedia) is also likely as the paper deals with the transmission of multimedia content (voice). cs.IT (Information Theory) is another possible category as the paper deals with the analysis of packet end-to-end delay. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) are less likely categories as the paper does not deal with cryptography or computational engineering, but they cannot be completely ruled out as the paper deals with the analysis of network performance and delay, which are relevant to these categories as well.
